<TEXT>
<P>
To the producers of China Beach: 
</P>
<P>
What have you done to my favorite Emmy-winning series this season? You have 
taken us backward and forward in time, confused us with unfocused plots and 
changed the characters so that they don't resemble those we've grown to know 
and love. 
</P>
<P>
You have turned the series into a farsical caricature of itself that is both 
overacted and underdirected. I, for one will no longer be staying home to watch 
my once favorite show. Change is good, camouflage is unforgivable. 
</P>
<P>
Susan McDonald, Studio City 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, (Orange County Edition) 1990's "China Beach" (with Debra Stricklin, 
left, and Dana Delany): It's different, but does that make it better? 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
