<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOWDOWN ON MOMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I saw the "High &amp; Low" exhibition on Oct. 13, and contrary to Knight's 
declaration that the exhibit is a "flop," I thoroughly enjoyed it, as did the 
huge crowd. 
</P>
<P>
But, then, we only represent about 99% of the people. We are not educated or 
sophisticated in art history or theory. 
</P>
<P>
What a treat it was to see Warhol's Campbell Soup series, Lichtenstein's 
vibrant "As I Opened Fire," Picasso's "Gertrude Stein" and Jenny Holzer's 
dramatic LED signs and tiles. 
</P>
<P>
I have been to the major museums around the world. Although I am not 
artistically knowledgeable by Mr. Knight's definition, I know what I like, and 
you know what? That's all that matters. 
</P>
<P>
MARLENE G. STEIN 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111190-0018 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 306092 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
