<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING BOAT CAPSIZES; 22 FEARED DROWNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLOMBO, Sri Lanka 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fishing boat ferrying marooned villagers across a flooded area capsized 
Friday and at least 22 people were feared drowned, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victims had been stranded in Talawilla by monsoon rains, according to 
police officials in nearby Wennappuwa, 30 miles north of Colombo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
