<P>
SOUTHLAND ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAL POLY SLO TUNES UP FOR PLAYOFFS, 26-10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, tuning up for its first NCAA Division II playoff 
appearance since 1980, defeated Millersville University (Pa.), 26-10, in a 
nonconference game Saturday at San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
The eighth-ranked Mustangs, co-champion of the Western Football Conference, 
finished the regular season 9-1, their best record since 1973. 
</P>
<P>
Millersville is 7-3. 
</P>
<P>
Senior running back Joe Fragiadakis gained 208 yards in 23 carries and scored 
three touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
University of San Diego 21, Azusa Pacific 10 -- Scott Sporrer rushed for 145 
yards in 20 carries and scored two touchdowns to lead the Toreros (7-2) over 
the Cougars (6-3) in a nonconference game at Azusa Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
Redlands 37, Whittier 7 -- Brian Harmon passed for 239 yards and three 
touchdowns as the Bulldogs (8-1, 5-0) defeated the Poets (0-9, 0-5) in a 
Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference game at Redlands. 
</P>
<P>
