<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HELIX GIRLS SWEEP THEIR VOLLEYBALL MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Playing for the last time at home, top-seeded Helix defeated Serra, 15-8, 15-6, 
15-1, in a San Diego Section Division II girls' volleyball quarterfinal match. 
The Highlanders improved their record to 30-0 and extended their record Section 
home victory streak to 29 matches. Karrie Downey had 12 kills and five aces to 
lead Helix. 
</P>
<P>
In another Division II girls' volleyball match: 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines d. Mar Vista, 15-4, 15-0, 16-14 -- Second-seeded Torrey Pines 
called time out at 4-4 in the first game, then scored 26 consecutive points. 
Amy Peters led Torrey Pines (23-2) with 11 kills. Mar Vista ended its season 
22-10. 
</P>
<P>
Water Polo 
</P>
<P>
First round 
</P>
<P>
3-A 
</P>
<P>
At Grossmont High 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Miguel 16, Bonita Vista 8 -- Sixth-seeded Mt. Miguel (15-12) never trailed, 
and Matt Berry scored six goals and Bill Throop five for the Matadors. Bonita 
Vista dropped to 13-13. 
</P>
<P>
Mira Mesa 14, Helix 12 (OT) -- Helix recovered from an 11-8 deficit with 2:49 
remaining to tie it, 11-11, before the overtime, in which the Highlanders were 
outscored, 3-1. No. 8 Mira Mesa improved to 16-10; Helix dropped to 12-12. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterfinals 
</P>
<P>
2-A 
</P>
<P>
At Mt. Carmel 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla 20, Army-Navy 6 -- Mike Nalu scored eight goals and teammates Eric 
Nielsen and John Allen added five and three goals for top-ranked Valhalla 
(20-4). Army-Navy fell to 13-9. 
</P>
<P>
USDHS 10, Carlsbad 7 -- For the No. 2 Dons, Doug Munz had five goals and Alex 
Chehansky added four. USDHS (15-9) led, 5-0, after the first quarter. Carlsbad 
finished its season 17-7. 
</P>
<P>
Girls' Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
Quarterfinals 
</P>
<P>
Division IV 
</P>
<P>
Bishop's d. Holtville, 15-2, 15-3, 15-11 -- Kaylie Orr (nine) and Jocelyn 
Eckhardt (seven) combined for 16 kills for No. 3 Bishop's, which improved to 
14-5. Holtville dropped to 8-9. 
</P>
<P>
Marian d. Mountain Empire, 15-7, 15-3, 13-15, 16-14 -- Visiting Marian (13-12) 
handed No. 4 Mountain Empire the loss. The Crusaders were led by Adanya Guevara 
with 10 kills and Georgette Esperanza with eight. 
</P>
<P>
Division V 
</P>
<P>
Francis Parker d. Lutheran, 15-1, 15-1, 15-7 -- No. 1 Francis Parker (9-0) made 
short work of Lutheran (4-11), moving to the semifinals in only 35 minutes. 
Emily Dawe had 12 aces and Amy Meier had eight kills in the winning effort. 
</P>
<P>
Football 
</P>
<P>
Desert Coastal League 
</P>
<P>
Army-Navy 20, Calipatria 7 -- James Reed rushed for 89 yards in 12 carries and 
had two touchdowns for Army-Navy, which gained 252 yards rushing and held 
Calipatria (3-6) to 169 yards on offense. With the victory, Army-Navy (8-0) won 
the league championship. 
</P>
