<P>
OAK PARK TRIPPED, 18-3, SETTLES FOR LEAGUE TITLE TIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB SONNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cheered on by the Carpinteria High football team, which had more than a slight 
interest in the outcome, Bishop Diego defeated Oak Park, 18-3, Saturday night 
in a Tri-Valley League game at San Marcos High. 
</P>
<P>
Oak Park (6-4, 3-1 in league play) must share the league title with 
Carpinteria. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Diego's Benito Rivera hauled in a 34-yard pass from Richie Donati in the 
first quarter to open the scoring. Howie Dougherty added a touchdown later in 
the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The only bright moment for Oak Park came in the second quarter on a 24-yard 
Mike Stern field goal. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Diego scored its final touchdown when Oak Park's Wes Lones fumbled the 
second-half kickoff and Danny Kendrick recovered the ball at the Eagle 28. 
Donati, 10 of 20 for 89 yards and one interception, then passed four yards for 
his second touchdown. ROB SONNER 
</P>
