<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL LEADERS FALL TO JONES AT VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
P. J. Jones of Rolling Hills drove to a 50-lap main-event victory in the U. S. 
Auto Club's National Midget race at Ventura Raceway on Saturday night on a 
wind-swept, super-slick quarter-mile dirt oval that produced numerous 
spin-outs. 
</P>
<P>
A field that included more than 70 cars also slowed the action as the program 
fell more than 90 minutes behind schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Jones, who finished seventh in the USAC Western States Series points standings, 
held off Jeff Gordon of Pittsboro, Ind., and Mike Streicher of Findlay, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
Gordon and Streicher finished second and third, respectively, although Gordon 
continues to lead the national points standings over Streicher, 463-451, with 
three races remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Gordon went wire to wire to win a 10-lap semi-main event and qualify for the 
feature. 
</P>
<P>
Still to be determined at press time was Jay Drake's bid to seal the Western 
States Series three-quarter Midget championship. Drake holds a 52-point lead 
over Cory Kruseman of Ventura. PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
