<TEXT>
<P>
Tokie Prainovic scored a goal from 10 meters out with 35 seconds left to play 
to give Cuesta College a 9-8 victory over Golden West in the Community College 
Southern California Regional water polo championship game at Belmont Plaza on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Prainovic had three goals and teammate Alex Asta had two for Cuesta (24-1). 
Golden West (28-4) was led by Edvard Van Luijin, who had four goals, and Jason 
Mills, who had two. 
</P>
<P>
It was a close game throughout. The score was tied at the end of the first 
(3-3) and third quarters (7-7) and at 8-8 before Prainovic's last goal. 
