</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Indonesians defeated the two remaining American men in the U.S. Open 
Badminton Championships singles competition Saturday at UC Irvine's Bren 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
Bambang Suprianto defeated Chris Jogis of Manhattan Beach, 15-10, 15-4, and 
top-seeded Fung Permadi beat Tariq Wadood of Redondo Beach, 15-1, 15-1, in the 
men's singles semifinals to advance to today's finals. 
</P>
<P>
In the mixed doubles semifinals, Traci Britton of Canada and Wadood teamed to 
beat Yao Ximing and Terry Lira of the United States, 15-8, 15-8, and Britton's 
Canadian husband, John, teamed with Yelena Rybkina of the Soviet Union to 
defeat Heinz Fischer of Austria and Diana Koleva of Bulgaria, 15-7, 17-14. 
