<HEADLINE>
<P>
A FITTING PUNISHMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego City Council's revocation of the opening of Pomerado Road ("S.D. 
Council Revokes Plan to Reopen Pomerado Road," Nov. 6) is petty and arrogant. 
</P>
<P>
Too bad about extra traffic coming through Scripps Ranch. Every community in 
greater San Diego has the same problem, but they don't fence off public 
streets. 
</P>
<P>
The city of San Diego and the council should be ashamed of being so 
small-minded. I sentence all of them to two hours of nonstop driving on I-15 at 
rush hour for at least six months. 
</P>
<P>
CHARLOTTE B. GORDON, San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
