<TEXT>
<P>
A youth who was killed in a drive-by shooting in Lawndale on Monday minutes 
after school let out has been identified as a Leuzinger High School student who 
recently joined a Filipino gang, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Delgado, 16, of Gardena, who sang in the school's top choir group since 
his freshman year, was shot in the head Monday by members of a rival Vietnamese 
gang as he waited with a group of friends for a ride home, said Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Detective Ed Milkey. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting, which occurred outside a house on 147th Street about one block 
from the Leuzinger campus, appeared to be in retaliation for a fistfight 
earlier in the day in which a large group of Filipino gang members beat up a 
Vietnamese gang member, Milkey said. 
</P>
<P>
That beating, in turn, was apparently in retaliation for a beating suffered by 
two Filipino gang members two weeks before, he said. 
</P>
<P>
"(Delgado) was a nice kid; he just joined the wrong group at the wrong time and 
was in the wrong place at the wrong time," Milkey said. 
</P>
<P>
Three crisis counselors from Robert F. Kennedy Medical Center spent Tuesday at 
Leuzinger High speaking to students who sang with Delgado in the choir. Members 
of the Leuzinger Select Chorale will sing at his funeral at St. Jerome's 
Catholic Church in Westchester on Monday morning. 
