<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOLDIER FROM TEXAS FOUND DEAD IN SHOWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EASTERN SAUDI ARABIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. Army soldier taking part in Operation Desert Shield has been found dead, 
apparently of natural causes, in a shower, military officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The soldier was identified as Sgt. James Wilcher, 25, by officials at Ft. 
Bliss, Tex., where he had been stationed earlier. They said he was found dead 
Thursday after dinner. 
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation showed no evidence of foul play, the Pentagon said. 
</P>
<P>
The soldier was assigned to the 118th Ordnance Detachment of the 11th Air 
Defense Artillery Brigade. 
</P>
