<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST : SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
NEWSLETTER TO CEASE PUBLICATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council agreed Wednesday to shut down the production of the city's 
newsletter, The South Pasadena Quarterly, after next year's summer issue, but 
promised to explore other methods of providing information to residents. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager John Bernardi said the newsletter, which is written by city staff 
members, has grown "dry" over the years, with oft-repeated articles and stories 
that have lost their timeliness by the time they are published. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Evelyn Fierro suggested that the quarterly could be replaced by a shorter 
monthly newsletter produced by professional journalists hired by the city. The 
council said the quarterly newsletter could be revived if no other substitutes 
are found by next June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
