<LENGTH>
<P>
123 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST : BALDWIN PARK; 
</P>
<P>
CHANGES IN DEVELOPMENT PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Officials are overhauling the city's 4-year-old Sierra Vista Development Plan 
because it is hindering the very development that it was meant to encourage. 
</P>
<P>
The development plan for the corridor along the 10 and 605 freeways was 
designed to foster larger-scale development in an area littered with small 
properties. 
</P>
<P>
City planner Lawrence Onaga told the City Council on Wednesday that development 
has stalled because developers have had difficulty assembling lots meeting 
their requirements. He recommended that land-size requirements be relaxed in 
certain areas and that design guidelines and a high-priority zone be 
established. Onaga said it would be several months before public hearings on 
the proposed changes would begin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
