<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALER FOR NEWSPAPER RECYCLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLINGSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We're learning once again how important it is to recycle newspapers along with 
glass, plastic and aluminum. 
</P>
<P>
With every ton of newspapers that is recycled, more than a dozen trees are 
saved! Here's a project that will make it easier for all of us to do our part, 
an easy-to-build paper baler. 
</P>
<P>
The baler holds about one month's accumulation of newspapers and is convenient 
to use with a built-in string box as well as a covered razor blade to cut the 
string or twine. Step-by-step directions and full-size traceable patterns make 
this project simple enough for the amateur woodworker. Just trace the parts, 
saw them out, and put them together! 
</P>
</TEXT>
