<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPEN HOUSES DEFENDED AS VALUABLE SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Weekend poen houses allow potential buyers to "preview" properties at a relaxed 
pace while answering the questions, "Do we like this neighborhood and 
community?" "Can we afford to buy here?" "Will this suit our lifestyle?" Agents 
aren't simply marketing one selelr's home that afternoon, but an entire way of 
life. 
</P>
<P>
In this already difficult market, if sellers don't have trust in the real 
estate professional's marketing advice and fail to cooperate on open houses, 
caravans and short-notice showings, it is tantamount to cutting off one's nose 
to spite one's face! 
</P>
<P>
SUSAN HEELEY, Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111190-0247 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 308563 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 11, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
